PARAGRAPH.#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES Convergys Corp. CVG swung to a third-quarter profit, with adjusted results declining but topping analysts' estimates, as the company rebounded from prior-year losses from discontinued operations. The provider of back-office services such as technical support and marketing research has seen its core results pressured lately by slumping demand since the economic downturn. It sold its human-resources management business in June for about $100 million. The company earlier Monday said it had reached an agreement with current President and Chief Executive Jeffrey Fox to continue in his roles, providing a yearly base salary of $300,000 as well as 4,500 shares of the company's stock per month, according to a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission.
